'''Leonard Insull''' (1883&ndash;1974) was [[United Kingdom|Britain's]] leading [[ventriloquism|ventriloquial figure]] maker of the twentieth century.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alansemok.com/dummies/insull.html|title=insull|work=The Dummy Doctor|accessdate=13 March 2012}}</ref>  He created many hundreds of items for Lewis Davenport Ltd.

Born in [[Wolverhampton]], Insull trained as a [[joiner]] before entering showbusiness as a magician, "Hinsle, the Comedy Illusionist".  He worked with his son, also Leonard, to construct ventriloquist's dummies until his son's death in 1957.<ref>"[http://www.doeandhope.com/products/a-fine-quality-mid-20th-ventriloquists-dummy-attributed-to-leonard-insull-afl21 A Fine Quality Mid 20th Ventriloquist's Dummy Attributed to Leonard Insull]", ''Doe & Hope''</ref>  His noted figures include [[Lord Charles]] for [[Ray Allen]] and [[Archie Andrews (puppet)|Archie Andrews]] for [[Peter Brough]].<ref>[[Roy Hudd]] and Philip Hindin, ''Roy Hudd's cavalcade of variety acts: a who was who of light entertainment, 1945-60'', p.3</ref>

